main event: An unidentified object was observed rising in the South and passing overhead to the North, resembling an ECHO but moving at a much faster speed.
interesting points: The observation was made on 7 August 1963 at Camp Kapitachouane, Canada., The report speculates that the object was either a balloon or an aircraft due to its speed and motion., It was noted that the object emitted a pale green light and approached the observer's location., The duration of the observation was not reported., The document appears to be part of an old UFO report from Project Blue Book.
witness description: a person observing the object from the ground
